  "What does De Moivre's Theorem state?": "",
  "[r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))]^n = r(cos(n*theta) + i sin(n*theta))": "",
  "[r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))]^n = r^n(cos(n*theta) + i sin(n*theta))": "",
  "[r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))]^n = r^n(cos(theta/n) + i sin(theta/n))": "",
  "[r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))]^n = nr(cos(n*theta) + i sin(n*theta))": "",
  "De Moivre's Theorem states that for any integer n, [r(cos(theta) + i sin(theta))]^n = r^n(cos(n*theta) + i sin(n*theta)). The modulus is raised to the nth power and the argument is multiplied by n.": "",
  "What is the meaning of 'nth roots of unity'?": "",
